data.title: Mid-Atlantic: Maryland: Governor Divorces - The New York Times
data.meta_description: Maryland Gov Parris Glendening and wife divorce; photo (S)
data.text: Gov. Parris N. Glendening and his wife, Frances Hughes Glendening, have divorced after nearly 25 years of marriage. In a statement, Mr. Glendening, who is 59, said, ''We wish each other well and each remain dedicated to careers in public service.'' Mr. Glendening, a Democrat, has been separated from his 50-year-old wife, a lawyer for the Federal Election Commission, since July 2000. In August, The Washington Post reported that the governor was involved with one of his aides. Gary Gately (NYT)
